Happy 1st birthday to my Christmas Eve Angel!🎂
It is wild to know that you have been here with us for a whole year- the most refining and wondrous year of my life.
I love you with all of my heart and soul.
Most days, I can still hardly believe that I have been given the privilege of being your mama.
Getting to love you and watch you blossom and grow is the most precious gift.
Happy birthday, Scarlette Rose.♥️

I really wanted to make a 2022 recap reel but as I began scrolling through the massive amounts of videos and pictures stored on my phone from the last year, I realized that I do not currently possess the emotional energy to even attempt to compile some sort of video that could encompass the highlights.
So instead, here are a few clips from last week when we took Scarlette to the snow for the first time. A day we very much treasure.
I could say more about this year than I could ever hope to fit in a caption so for now I’ll just say this:
I am immensely grateful for 2022. 
The pain, the joy, the learning, the loving- The beauty of it all.
Thank you to the friends and family that held us this year.

#2022 #newyear #newyearseve

Happy 7th anniversary to my love and best friend.♥️
Sometimes I can’t believe we’ve been married for 7 years, and other times I feel like I’ve known you my whole life.
I truly cannot imagine life without you.
No matter what is happening in the world or within me, you are my steady and constant north star. You are my home and there isn’t a single day that passes that I don’t think about what an irreplaceable gift I have in you as my partner.
I hope that I can always offer you the same amount of love, comfort, and intention that you give so selflessly.
To many more beautiful years & memories.✨🥂

I know I've been pretty quiet here lately.
I've needed to take a break for my mental health which is *not* doing well.
I'm seeking help where I can think to but there is a lot going on right now.
I will share more when I'm ready because I (usually) love connecting and I want you to know you're not alone if you're in a similar place.
If you are feeling low, for any reason or just inexplicably, know that I am holding you close to my heart and wishing you to be loved and resourced.

We were hosted at the loveliest hotel during our first trip to New York- The Walker Hotel Greenwich Village. @walkerhotels 

Luckily for my Christmas-loving heart, they still had their holiday decor up when we got there!
As soon as we walked through the double doors, we could feel the warmth and welcoming of the lobby.
The staff was incredibly friendly- Truly the most friendly and helpful hotel staff that I have ever encountered.

Adam and I both celebrated our birthdays while we were there too!(Mine is the 15th, his the 16th)
We had my birthday brunch at the hotel’s restaurant, @societycafenyc plus a couple other meals {via room service} and the food was excellent.

All in all, it was a perfect stay.
The hotel was central to everything and a welcomed respite after traipsing around the city all day.

Thank you so much for having us @walkerhotels 
I can’t wait to visit again!🌆✨♥️

#walkerhotelgreenwichvillage #walkerhotels #greenwichvillage #nyc #newyorkcity

Just reminiscing about our trip to New York and the amazing time we had staying at @walkerhotels in Greenwich Village.

To the best baby, dog, and cat daddy there is... @adam.f.rupp

I find myself marveling at you daily.
Your strength and patience, the way you play and take in all of the little moments with such joy, your willingness to help with anything and everything...

At the close of June, we said goodbye to our home of the last three years.
It’s the longest that Adam and I have lived in one place together. It was Scarlette’s first home and a place that I found solace during one of the darkest seasons of my life.

I have been grieving this move since before we left.
Despite being 8 months pregnant, the move was a financial necessity and couldn’t be put off any longer.
But, oh my heart...it has been so tender and heavy as we’ve been working to settle into our new place. It doesn’t feel like home.

There’s so much on my mind about this transition but my main purpose in sharing is these two things:
♥️I wanted to honor the place that I have loved and been loved in for the last three years.
Although it’s painful, it fills me with so much gratitude as I reflect over those years and it guides me toward the closure that I know I need to move forward.
♥️If you feel like everyone’s life is moving in an upward trajectory while yours is taking steps back, you are not alone.
It has felt backwards and upside down to be getting older, growing our family, and simultaneously feel like things are regressing...To not see certain dreams or plans come to fruition when we hoped they would.
In hindsight, we know life often doesn’t work that way. But I know for me personally, it can be easy to lose sight of that in a world dominated by social media and it’s idyllic circumstances that are curated before us daily.
So if you’re in a similar place, know that I am there with you, holding space for you.

✨To our beloved little townhome on Garfield Ave... Thank you.
You will always hold such a special place in my heart.
Thank you to my husband and our friends that filled it with so much joy and irreplaceable memories. It was an honor and a privilege to be held in those four walls and on that sprawling green grass...✨
